reviews.text: This is the worst Subway to DINE IN at. The EMPLOYEES are terrible. I ordered food and ate here on Thursday for lunch. I had to head to work after, so I brought my clothing to change into. I used the restroom once before I ate and then I wanted to use it again once I was done so that I could change into my uniform and touch up on my makeup. As I'm approaching the bathroom, three employees come from behind the counter and tell me that I can no longer use the bathroom again. I asked why not? I'm a paying customer, I just want to change and touch up my make up. He told me that if I wanted to do that, then I should GO HOME. Then they started asking how long I wanted to use the bathroom for. At this point I grew livid. When I asked to speak to the manager they refused. I asked who the owner was and they refused that as well. Then they said that I needed to leave or they would call the police on me. Call the police on me for what? For trying to use the bathroom at a place that I spent my money at? Or call the police on me for asking to speak to a manager for being treated poorly? It was absolutely unacceptable. And I did go off.

They've added pizza, pasta bowls and boneless wings to their menu. The only thing I had not tried was their wings. But as far as the rest of the menu, I have not picked anything I did not like. Great additions to a already scrumptious menu of sandwiches
It is 9:45am and this store is not open which is supposed to be open at 9:00am I took a detour to get to this location which is a very big inconvenience!

Typical, no matter where you go. It's the same, not a healthy option only thing I like about subway is the cookies and snacks. Unhealthy prepackaged meat is what they use and it's way too salty and you still have to pay extra for more meat, as always they put very little on their subs unless you pay extra for the Unhealthy salty extra meat slices which again are prepackaged meat, not fresh at all. And you get charged way too much!
Honestly I was dissapointed. The people were kind of nice... but the whole area felt uncomfortable.
Good Food better then most chains. Service was very good she was so nicee the waitress. Washington DC is alright in my book!
Went with a friend of mine for lunch. I had the chicken and waffles. Large portions and very good indeed. She had pancakes, eggs and bacon. No complaints.
Sadly, I believe that this IHOP is now perminitly closed and has been sold. Just praying that it doesn't become a tobacco or liquor store!

reviews.author_name: I SLAY ALL DAY TRAVEL The Solo Traveler
reviews.text: This place was not bad at all and similar to any ihop (just a great place to eat). The food was delicious and I enjoyed myself.  I took myself here Saturday for breakfast.  It may be in SE DC but was a great spot to dine.  I love my steak and cheese and french fries, its the best!

This establishment is GHETTO. Second time here, we waited 7 minutes to even be greeted for a seat, then the young lady picked up the menus and walked off without saying a word!!!! Am I suppose to follow you? Then another 10 minutes for the sever to come to even take drink orders. Then there was a huge argument between customers and the staff. It was horrible people started leaving. If it wasn’t for my daughter wanting these cinnastack pancakes I would have walked out too. Now I’m sitting here going on 8 minutes for a check. They won’t get anymore of my money for sure. HORRIBLE!!!!
I find this station's prices competitive and most times, lower than other major stations w/in 5 miles.  While the property attracts a lot of "foot traffic, for the most part, I feel relatively safe.

If this is the gas station that's located on Wheeler and Southern avenue only thing I can say is be prepared anything gos  and watch your back while you up there 🤷 I gave it two stars because the gas attendance is always nice
Too many people hang out up there Safety is a issue for me.
Unsafe location, drug addicts homeless and mentally unstable individuals. Not safe during the day nor night you never know what will pop off. Very violently active place
Dont go to this station at nite, not very well lit.  There are too many people hanging out asking to pump gas and panhandling.   Not safe

I didn't not order in Eddie carryout this environment is a very unhealthy place.  I just ordered bottle soda I was only in the area because I went to my financial institution that was in the area so I went to the closest laundromat which was Eddie's. Alot of African American males smoking and drinking blocking the business in the area.
It’s cool I guess for some wings and fries

I'm not from DC and I've never heard of a Chinese restaurant making cheese steaks ( in DC talk, steak n cheese) but this place gets it right! I loved the cheese steak egg rolls and have ordered 5 times already. Delicious and highly recommend this place!

Been eating here since I’ve been pregnant wit my first born and that’s been alittle over 5years now. Pregnant now wit my second and I just can’t get enough of they’re food is made with love! I love how patient they are. They are  not like them other carryouts that rush u on the phone and make u feel uncomfortable.........love it!
The 1/2 fish sub has more bread than fish.  Barely 1 piece of Whiting fish on numerous occasions lately,had to toss out a lot of roll.  Will not be going back.  Have eaten from their for years

Can you eat just the pizza crust without any ranch from here? Possibly but I would say it's similar to like a Papa John's so you might want to ask for ranch however they use Ken's ranch which is okay but it's store bought it's not homemade so it's not really the greatest if you have a bottle of ranch you're better off saving your money.

I wanted to order a margarita pizza but it was not available through the online ordering process so I just went with a pepperoni because at least it's one of the easier pizzas for anybody to make.

Ingredients: the quality was actually just okay it's probably sourced from Cisco and you can taste that it is commercial grade in quality. The sauce was too acidic from using unripe tomatoes and gave me bad heart burn. This only happens to me with bad sauce. I do not know how often they make their sauce and where they source their ingredients from but I won't be trying any other pizzas from here.

Execution of cooking: it was properly cooked and the crust is perfectly crisp but lacking flavor of good dough.

Presentation: not good, either it was because it is during a lunch rush although it should have been towards the end of it or the employee just doesn't care and threw pepperoni on it where are some slices don't have nearly as much as others. Also when they cut the pizza it was not cut all the way through requiring a knife or additional effort to tear the slices apart.

Only giving 2 stars because customer service was not bad food was burnt took an 1+ to get it redelivered I have already feed my niece and nephews something else ….so the food was no longer need came and my wrap was still disgusting will never order from here again I’ve been eating here for 3 years now it got worst n worst n I kept letting it slide will never eat here will drive to naylor road location first.

Trash! Waited over an hour for a pizza, just for the driver to call and said he left it and that I would need to call and make another order or have them send another driver. Then when I called the store, whomever answered the phone rudely said "what do you want me to do about it!?" and hung up. I called back two more times and was hung up on each time. Then the stopped answering the phone. Trash service

Waited two hours for a pizza and I'm 7 minutes away. so I decided to come up there and you have one of the workers outside smoking and my pizza is sitting there meanwhile I'm told the driver is on his way.
I did a delivery order. The delivery driver was such a nice and humble person. He called and showed up on time. The food was nice and hot. I think he said his name is Dominique. We liked the service.

Soooo...  I dunno.  I dunno why this place gets a bad rep.  Not sure if it's the shift people go on, the hours or what but the couple times I've been, it's been magnificent, both times.
The only complaint, was the guy working in the back was working with food, with a big beard and no beard guard on...  The place wasn't perfectly clean but clean enough.  It was dinner rush, after all.  The place was crowded, with a line to the door but they were moving people at a pretty good clip...  The food was hot.  They weren't stingy with the meats and cheese and the container (I got a bowl), was stuffed full and hot!  It was enough for me and my partner to eat out of, and both to be full.  Again, no idea what the bad press is about but they've done me right and they've definitely earned themselves a loyal customer. 🥰

Now, I try to be fair and I'm always honest. This Chipotle location is lackluster and has gone down. I've both ordered from Uber Eats (which is more expensive) and I've physically gone inside. The customer service is very unacceptable and the food portions are skim compared to the price that they want you to pay. Newsflash, we all are suffering in this pandemic and economic crisis; The fact that people still spend money out to eat to help support local businesses is a blessing. CUSTOMERS DESERVE BETTER SERVICE! I just ordered again today  ( before being completely done with this location); I ordered two chicken bowls . The food was cold and the portion looked like it was made for a toddler, it looks like someone ate out of the carton. No guacamole, which was an extra charge ..a sprinkle of cheese, no meat... It was supposed to be chicken in it ...  Where is the food? My order was over $40. I'm done.

BOTH THESE EMPLOYEES ARE RUDE! this man in the first picture said that they didn’t have the big wrap for the burrito as they were using something else just to say I couldn’t get it then says he thought it was common sense! If you didn’t have the wrap and weren’t making them at all that should’ve been said he proceeded to curse and get upset because I told him his communication is off and needs to improve if he’s working fast food then I asked the lady whose in the picture for his name after she heard him use profanity she told me no which she can’t do and then told security to have me leave after I took pictures of them which I can do because this is my phone!

Alabama Ave Chipotle. More like hard working Chipotle. Food prep, conditions and customer service is good. The amount of patrons served and catered to is well compared to the massive lines that dine here. I even made a juicy burrito and the staff were able to cleanly and skillfully prepare my meal.  Now I myself wouldn't necessarily sit to dine, the option is available.

They need to make this a mobile pick up location ONLY. Everytime I go to this location i get stoped at the door and told "its mobile pick up only".  They are not convenient at all. And i usually dont have issue with their old staff but their new staff who seem to be spanish have been very rude  (ignored me and a lady that was infront of me while he fulfilled a mobile order and then talked to us like we was bothering them). If they don't like their job just leave but don't be rude to customers, especially when they are paying customers. Please hire new staff and management or just make this a mobile pick up location.

A hidden treasure of our community. FRESH, delicious foods. Excellent service, I see how hard you work and how easy you make it look. You are appreciated and shows with our business. THANKS for food I trust!❤️😋😜

After living on this side of town for almost 1yr, today I've decided to step foot in this spot FOR THE FIRST TIME. My initial thoughts were not pleasant because the outside looks run down (it's the hood for you). But when I stepped inside and took my order it wasn't bad at all (just need a little renovation). Overall the food was good enough to eat again. My order was a bacon and egg sandwich with home fries and it wasn't what I expected, it exceeded my expectations. I guess you should never judge a book by its cover without doing my research!!!
Bussin'!! Especially the breakfast :) Also, very sweet people and fast with the order. I recommend  the Hungry Man with Frenchtoast. Can typically  feed two people frfr unless you're  greedy
Need to update restaurants customer service excellent atmosphere could be a little more enjoyable

Came with my daughter as she purchased the sausage, egg& cheese on croissant roll with butter and grape jelly. Imma have to get me one next time I come cause that joint looked and smelled good. Plus she crushed
I brought 10 wings and fries on 1-27/23 and the chicken was spoiled it smelled like ammonia I ate 1 piece and spit it out because it tasted funny and then I smelled 🤮🤮

Hi, I tried this place for the first time and sadly I was highly disappointed with their chicken gyro. The sauce tasted weird as well as the chicken and after two bites, I had to just throw it away. I also purchased 3 wings with fries and both were ok. To me, the fried wings could have used a little more seasoning but that’s coming from a person who likes my food well seasoned. So overall I rated them a 3 because parking was convenient and the guy that helped with my order was very pleasant but that gyro could use some major changes.

I paid $11 and some change for a grilled chicken salad with an additional chicken breast.  The chicken was fried and tasted like it had gone off a while back.  There was barely any chicken on the salad and for some reason there were several slices of lemon in it with their produce stickers still attached.  My first hint should’ve been the big “NO REFUNDS OR EXHANGES” sign on the window.  Maybe even the fact that there was debris all over the restaurant and fuel injector cleaner was sold right next to the food.  Or maybe how the owner walked around in flip flops and wiped his sweat with a kitchen rag.  Do NOT GO.

I traveled here TWICE. I told the worker no mayo on my burger, he did it anyway. I sent it back & he still did it wrong but no mayo this time. The 2nd time, i tried a steak and cheese. No mayo. I wrote it down so it would be no problem and they overcharged me and made it wrong again. I will never ever be back here! NEVER
Great food and customer service a jewel in the neighborhood prices are good too

A lot of people stand around in front of the carry out and sometimes inside, but it doesn’t feel dangerous (-1 star). The order takers are friendly given they have been in the community for years. Everything I have ordered has been pretty good. I usually order the same things every time I stop through; Shrimp Egg Rolls, Chicken Tenders with Fries, Wings, or Shrimp Fried Rice. I especially like the Tenders. They’re always nice a hot with real breast meat.

** They do take debit/credit cards with a 3.5% fee added to your total
Been eating out of here for at least 30 yrs .food been good customer service is good.and they know me on sight and my voice

Food is trash ain’t how it used to be 9-10 years ago it’s trash the chicken seem like they rush nd cook my chicken the fries was the only thing good.. their steak nd cheese was so nasty nd the cheese seem so watery idk it wasn’t good..
ShoutOut to Tony and Mama Saun✌️5 wing N fries been on point for yrs💯..."you like salt, pepper, mumbo sauce"..."okay fi' ninty-fi"😉

All I can say is don't judge a book by its cover. I frequent this place whenever I come into town. Best steak & cheese subs hands down. Wings are huge and mumbo sauce is there best. Unfortunately it's in a very bad location. Still worth a trip for some of DC's local foods!
